Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #shallow dish{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}; pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until about 1⁄2 inch thick. Season all over with @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Brush chicken all over with @smoky mustard{1%ounce}. Working one piece at a time, press chicken into seasoned panko until fully coated on both sides.

Heat a 1⁄4-inch layer of oil in a large, #heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat.

Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to the pan, add coated chicken in a single layer. Cook until panko is golden and chicken is cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side (you may need to work in batches for 4 servings).

> TIP: Reduce heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings), juice from half the lemon, salt, and pepper.

Halve and toast @potato bun{2}.

Fill buns with chicken and slaw.

Divide sandos between plates. Serve with roasted carrots and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.